'From then on I used to call myself Clare Kane. I was seventeen years old. Truth. I grew up in Scarsdale, New York. Truth. I recently moved to Hermosa Beach, California. Truth. We moved here because of my father’s transfer. Lie. My life was intact and normal. Lie. At that time I didn't know that I was supposed to be someone else. That Clare Kane was one big lie.'Seventeen-year-old Clare Kane moves from New York to California to forget what happened to her best friend Isabel. Just after Isabel’s funeral nobody seems to remember her. Clare is the only one who hardly believes that Isabel never existed. While trying to discover what really happened to Isabel, death is being close on her heels. Only Asher seems to understand Clare until everything falls apart and she has troubles to differentiate between reality and illusion.